<br>
I recently joined Clan Bloodtalon to hang out with Attaru (one of the founding members) and to have some place for my new characters here on Tunare to grow.  I am transferring my only remaining level 65 enchanter &lt;gnomie <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  &gt; from Tholuxe Palles soon.  I have played the game since beta, been a part of many wonderful guilds, some bad guilds and some ok guilds.  Created a couple (two of which still thrive today on PvP servers) and helpped create a couple.  I have seen guilds start small and itricate then grow and thrive, I've seen guilds start out huge just inviting everyone and blow up, I've seen all sorts of growing pains, splits, defections, mutanies, explosions and advances.  Been to PoTime, hung out in the elementals, done ALOT of tradescrafting.  BUT, I am not all knowing <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  I'm just a guy &lt;mr. mom&gt; that has lots of free time, so here is my point.<br>
<br>
<br>
Clan Bloodtalon has the longevity of name and the core resources to be a GREAT guild.  Many of the players are capable and even more willing to contribute and learn.  The one thing that is lacking is ORGANIZATION.  OMG if that isn't the ABSOLUTE hardest thing to obtain in this type of environment I dont know what is.  I am willing, with the consent of the officer core and leadership and the support of the member base to suggest and help impliment changes that will bring a bit more order to the guild and allow members to receive more benefit from hold the title Clan Bloodtalon above thier head.  I'm not a militarist, I can't do the totalitarian thing....but I can recommend certain things that will be manditory for base membership and then further things for members to be comfortable and able to get the support in thier endeavors that they want and need.<br>
<br>
The first move is to know who and what we are dealing with and in doing so gain more of an understanding as to what capacity we have in means of raiding, long term camps, source camps (camps you use to get items for many members such as keys....medallions etc) and ToO  &lt;T.o.O. is simply Target of Oppourtunity&gt;  so if you are willing to put in a little time on the message boards and willing to rise to the challenge of aiding your brothers in arms then help us here by posting the following info<br>
<br>
<br>
You MAIN character<br>
Any Alts you have in the guild<br>
The best time for you to play<br>
Are you a casual player (less than 10 hours a week)<br>
Are you a junkie (every night for at least 4 hours)<br>
<br>
this is generic info shouldn't be hard to think up and post, once  I get in more with the big guns that  run the guild more will follow <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
<br>
PS  next thursday, cable permitting and enough sign'n up...i will host a Kael Raid....look for it under the raid section....THANKS<br>
<br>
<br>
Drixos<br>
44 Bard of Clan Bloodtalon &lt;yeah yeah i gotta make a sig&gt;<br>
